00:47:07,880 --> 00:47:09,940
So let's look at the major thinkers.

784
00:47:10,040 --> 00:47:13,960
You have Homer. You have the playwrights,

785
00:47:13,960 --> 00:47:16,620
Aeschylus, Sophocles, and Euboides.

786
00:47:16,920 --> 00:47:19,240
And you have the philosophers,
Plato and Aristotle.

787
00:47:19,540 --> 00:47:21,200
And you have the philosophers,
Plato and Aristotle. Alright.

788
00:47:22,640 --> 00:47:24,960
So the Greeks created a
new way of being a human.

789
00:47:25,160 --> 00:47:27,600
Alright. Alright.

790
00:47:27,600 --> 00:47:28,960
Alright. Alright. Alright.

791
00:47:34,880 --> 00:47:38,100
Alright. Alright. Alright.
Alright. Alright. Alright.

792
00:47:39,100 --> 00:47:40,480
Alright. Alright. Alright. Alright.

793
00:47:40,480 --> 00:47:42,220
Alright. Alright.

794
00:47:44,340 --> 00:47:51,140
Alright. Because

795
00:47:51,140 --> 00:47:56,980
the point of listening to Homer
was to enter Homer's world

796
00:47:56,980 --> 00:47:58,760
and become Achilles or Odysseus.

797
00:47:58,980 --> 00:48:01,660
And through this process, you
became a different person.

798
00:48:02,320 --> 00:48:05,260
And therefore, you learned empathy,

799
00:48:05,480 --> 00:48:07,320
but you also expanded your imagination.

800
00:48:08,320 --> 00:48:13,640
Okay? So that's what
