812
00:48:52,760 --> 00:48:54,060
There's a debate going on.

813
00:48:54,680 --> 00:48:58,820
You have to switch perspectives in
order to understand the characters.

814
00:48:59,260 --> 00:49:03,360
And this creates the capacity
for an inner monologue.

815
00:49:03,560 --> 00:49:04,920
Okay? And a debate in you.

816
00:49:06,600 --> 00:49:08,780
And then you have Plato and Aristotle.

817
00:49:09,180 --> 00:49:11,160
What Plato did that

818
00:49:11,160 --> 00:49:15,940
was unique was he took all
the dialogue in the play.

819
00:49:16,360 --> 00:49:18,480
And he transported it onto the page.

820
00:49:19,240 --> 00:49:21,940
But now, you're reading it by yourself.

821
00:49:22,340 --> 00:49:24,760
And you have the benefit of time.

822
00:49:26,000 --> 00:49:28,580
Okay? And so,

823
00:49:28,680 --> 00:49:32,460
this creates a capacity
for reason and reflection.

824
00:49:33,900 --> 00:49:38,980
Okay? You can sort of reason out
